						               													<description>Heard the News is a money market simulation (corporate stocks and currency exchanges in each of five countries). Game play consists of 10 rounds, each of which includes four phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1) Read the news (from one of six pre-arranged sets of cards).  This news tells global facts as well as specific information about each region of the world&amp;#10;&amp;#10;2) Each player moves around up to two of their stock tokens (they have 4)--selling and buying.  Their actions alter the prices of the stocks and/or currencies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;3) Do step 2 again&amp;#10;&amp;#10;4) Turn over the news card to see how each of the five corporate stocks changed (up a little, down a little, or stays put).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;That's it.  Play 10 rounds, liquidate stocks and money holdings, and see who has the most points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
